00:26:01,939 --> 00:26:06,760
Even a dumb geezer knows...
- Just move on. No one was killed.

249
00:26:06,860 --> 00:26:08,987
Ask him.

250
00:26:09,863 --> 00:26:13,534
Don't bark at me.
I didn't name you.

251
00:26:13,700 --> 00:26:17,770
We will. And if he can't,
we'll come back and ask you.

252
00:26:17,870 --> 00:26:24,835
Hey. I come from hell. My grandma
has got more attitude than you.

253
00:26:25,002 --> 00:26:28,657
Go shake down a 7-1 1 for a day-old wiener.

254
00:26:28,798 --> 00:26:33,302
There's a painting of one of the guys.

255
00:26:36,012 --> 00:26:41,643
I've been praying for him.
- I'm on my way to the hospital.

256
00:26:41,810 --> 00:26:46,022
Just watch the dog for tonight.
- No, no.

257
00:26:46,189 --> 00:26:49,067
I'm sorry.
- Thanks.

258
00:26:50,652 --> 00:26:54,947
Old bitch. Damn dog.

259
00:26:58,200 --> 00:27:00,953
You're taking him.

260
00:27:01,120 --> 00:27:03,288
Get out of the way.

261
00:27:03,455 --> 00:27:06,542
Even the books.

262
00:27:07,376 --> 00:27:09,376
Wait.

263
00:27:09,962 --> 00:27:13,632
Do you want to say no to me?

264
00:27:18,970 --> 00:27:22,473
I don't want to say nothing to you.

265
00:27:22,890 --> 00:27:29,439
Because I've never felt this crazy.
I almost want you to say no.

266
00:27:32,817 --> 00:27:34,968
Thanks for looking after him.

267
00:27:35,068 --> 00:27:42,033
Hey. Where are you going?
- You don't want to mess with me.

268
00:27:42,200 --> 00:27:47,205
I can't take a dog.
Nobody's been in here before.

269
00:27:50,876 --> 00:27:53,420
Hey, Frank.

270
00:28:16,900 --> 00:28:20,236
One, two, three, four...

271
00:28:40,047 --> 00:28:42,674
You're dead.

272
00:28:42,841 --> 00:28:46,678
We don't have no dog food here.

273
00:28:46,845 --> 00:28:51,433
You'll eat what we got.
What we eat.

274
00:29:00,524 --> 00:29:02,985
Don't you do anything.

275
00:29:17,791 --> 00:29:20,293
Where's the trust?

276
00:29:29,678 --> 00:29:33,139
Never a break.

277
00:30:04,919 --> 00:30:06,919
God.

278
00:30:07,046 --> 00:30:11,951
We're halfway through the show
and we haven't sold a painting.

279
00:30:12,051 --> 00:30:15,345
No, we can't reduce the price.

280
00:30:15,512 --> 00:30:20,642
I'm in a free fall here.
- We can see him.

281
00:30:21,852 --> 00:30:25,188
I'll meet you in there, okay?

282
00:30:27,357 --> 00:30:29,357
Thank you.

283
00:30:31,987 --> 00:30:36,599
How are you doing, great one?
- I haven't looked at myself yet.

284
00:30:36,699 --> 00:30:41,287
I figured I could tell from your reaction.

285
00:30:42,121 --> 00:30:46,083
That bad?
- I talked to the doctor and...

286
00:30:49,962 --> 00:30:56,009
It's not that bad. The doctors say
you'll be your old self again.

287
00:30:56,176 --> 00:31:00,722
The scars might... Oh, shit.

288
00:31:06,519 --> 00:31:08,519
Jackie...

289
00:31:08,646 --> 00:31:11,774
Hand me a mirror, please.

290
00:31:19,364 --> 00:31:23,285
Wait. I have a smaller one.

291
00:31:33,294 --> 00:31:36,631
So how are things, anyway?

292
00:31:36,797 --> 00:31:42,428
How is Verdell?
- Mr. Udall... taking care of him.

293
00:31:42,637 --> 00:31:48,267
How could you? He'll hurt him.
- No, I promise.

294
00:31:48,434 --> 00:31:53,338
Not a chance. I own this guy.
Besides, there was nobody else.

295
00:31:53,438 --> 00:31:56,399
I'm always on the move and...

296
00:31:56,566 --> 00:31:59,402
Trust me.

297
00:31:59,569 --> 00:32:04,324
You are certain my dog is okay?
- Yes, your dog is fine.

298
00:32:11,206 --> 00:32:14,625
Waiting gives the devil time.

299
00:32:31,141 --> 00:32:33,976
Oh, my.

300
00:32:43,778 --> 00:32:46,698
Where did I go?

301
00:32:47,824 --> 00:32:50,993
That's your dog?
- No.

302
00:32:51,953 --> 00:32:55,122
What are you doing with a dog?

303
00:32:55,455 --> 00:33:00,252
Suckered in, set up.
- You're not worried he'll be taken?

304
00:33:02,879 --> 00:33:06,383
No, not until now.

305
00:33:06,550 --> 00:33:10,470
Sorry.
- I'm going to sit here.

306
00:33:10,637 --> 00:33:13,097
Hey, puppy.

307
00:33:13,889 --> 00:33:17,351
It's so cute.

308
00:33:17,518 --> 00:33:20,521
I wonder what breed he is.

309
00:33:24,066 --> 00:33:29,166
He's a little dog. If Bryan's not
here, you can bring him in.

310
00:33:31,574 --> 00:33:34,242
How old are you?

311
00:33:34,409 --> 00:33:37,871
To guess by your eyes... 50.

312
00:33:38,413 --> 00:33:42,734
By your eyes, I'd say you were kind.
So much for eyes.

313
00:33:42,834 --> 00:33:47,213
How old are you?
You brought it up. I'm curious.

314
00:33:47,422 --> 00:33:52,343
Not that you're ugly.
- I can take the compliment.

315
00:33:52,510 --> 00:33:57,164
But my knees start knocking when
you turn on the charm full blast.

316
00:33:57,264 --> 00:34:00,893
What's with the dark?

317
00:34:03,312 --> 00:34:05,522
Dawn patrol.

318
00:34:05,689 --> 00:34:09,484
My son had a full-blown attack.

319
00:34:09,651 --> 00:34:14,989
And for extra fun
they gave us the wrong antibiotics.

320
00:34:15,156 --> 00:34:17,992
No.

321
00:34:18,159 --> 00:34:22,288
It's bacon for the dog.

322
00:34:24,123 --> 00:34:28,444
Last week I was playing the piano
for him. And he likes it.

323
00:34:28,544 --> 00:34:35,008
So I decide I'm going to make a little joke.

324
00:34:43,934 --> 00:34:48,188
It's a beautiful day for our walk.

325
00:35:00,199 --> 00:35:03,786
Look at that dog.

326
00:35:03,952 --> 00:35:08,999
I've got to give you something real good.

327
00:35:09,500 --> 00:35:13,252
I'm going to show it to you.

328
00:35:14,504 --> 00:35:17,465
Don't be like me.

329
00:35:17,632 --> 00:35:23,388
Stay as you are. You're perfect.
I'll get you something to eat.

330
00:35:25,473 --> 00:35:28,643
I'd like to be treated like that.

331
00:35:29,977 --> 00:35:34,314
Let's go home and do some writing.

332
00:35:35,607 --> 00:35:40,278
'He had made the girl happy.
And what a girl.'

333
00:35:40,695 --> 00:35:44,157
'You've saved my life, she said.'

334
00:35:45,659 --> 00:35:49,162
'You'd better make it up to me.'

335
00:35:52,040 --> 00:35:58,003
Done.
Yes, I hate the doggie.

336
00:35:59,171 --> 00:36:02,466
62 books. Done.

337
00:36:03,217 --> 00:36:08,722
We have to cut back all expenses.
- He has no medical insurance?

338
00:36:08,889 --> 00:36:13,935
These are the food receipts,
the household expenses.

339
00:36:14,102 --> 00:36:17,856
Here's one for the dog again.
- I got it.

340
00:36:18,064 --> 00:36:21,109
And all the laundry.

341
00:36:23,319 --> 00:36:30,118
Boy, look at that.
He likes it at Chez Melvin.

342
00:36:31,536 --> 00:36:36,064
What are you coming over here for?
I can't cook with a dog near me.

343
00:36:36,164 --> 00:36:42,588
Just sit. We don't want any company.
I'll read you Emerson.

344
00:36:54,223 --> 00:37:00,062
How's Verdell doing?
- He's a pain in the ass.

345
00:37:03,941 --> 00:37:10,531
Simon's home. Can you keep the dog
until he's had a chance to adjust?

346
00:37:10,698 --> 00:37:15,327
It's been weeks and weeks.
A few more won't matter.

347
00:37:15,493 --> 00:37:20,957
He wants him back right away.
He'll be by tomorrow.

348
00:37:22,792 --> 00:37:26,546
Okay.

349
00:37:32,134 --> 00:37:35,387
Hungry? Be right with you.

350
00:38:38,864 --> 00:38:40,864
Mr. Udall.

351
00:38:46,288 --> 00:38:50,709
Some face they left hanging on you.
You look like...

352
00:38:50,876 --> 00:38:54,671
Could you take it...

353
00:38:55,630 --> 00:38:58,842
...just a little easy, Mr. Udall?

354
00:39:02,095 --> 00:39:04,095
Thank you.

355
00:39:06,766 --> 00:39:09,185
Verdell.

356
00:39:10,603 --> 00:39:14,773
Come here, my beautiful boy.
Come here.

357
00:39:14,940 --> 00:39:18,360
Let's go home and get well.

358
00:39:19,486 --> 00:39:25,011
I can't blame him for being weird.
Look at yourself in the mirror.

359
00:39:28,954 --> 00:39:31,206
Thank you.

360
00:39:34,417 --> 00:39:37,378
Come on, sweetheart.

361
00:39:37,545 --> 00:39:40,923
Verdell, come here.

362
00:39:43,050 --> 00:39:46,053
I know what you want.

363
00:39:49,724 --> 00:39:52,267
Where's my boy?

364
00:39:57,731 --> 00:40:01,484
No, don't force him.

365
00:40:33,222 --> 00:40:37,643
Over a dog.

366
00:40:38,311 --> 00:40:41,898
Over an ugly dog.

367
00:40:49,030 --> 00:40:53,784
Worst sidewalk in New York.
Look where they put it.

368
00:41:00,332 --> 00:41:05,253
Help.
- You'll make an appointment.

369
00:41:05,420 --> 00:41:09,491
How can you diagnose someone as
an obsessive-compulsive disorder -...

370
00:41:09,591 --> 00:41:12,660
...and then act like I had a choice
about barging in?

371
00:41:12,760 --> 00:41:16,288
You must leave.
- You said you could help me.

372
00:41:16,388 --> 00:41:21,811
What was that? A tease?
- If you take responsibility...

373
00:41:22,019 --> 00:41:26,023
You changed the room around.
- Two years ago.

374
00:41:26,190 --> 00:41:30,261
I also grew a beard, but you're
not interested in changes in me.

375
00:41:30,361 --> 00:41:34,431
I don't have a mountain of time.
I have to get to my restaurant.

376
00:41:34,531 --> 00:41:38,827
Do you know how hard it was for me
to come here?

377
00:41:40,203 --> 00:41:42,668
No, we're not doing this now.

378
00:41:42,747 --> 00:41:47,836
I changed just one pattern,
as you always said I should.

379
00:41:48,044 --> 00:41:50,463
No. Nope.

380
00:41:59,721 --> 00:42:04,518
What if this is as good as it gets?

381
00:42:16,279 --> 00:42:19,490
What the heck are those for?

382
00:42:21,409 --> 00:42:24,537
No, no, no. Get Carol.

383
00:42:24,704 --> 00:42:30,543
I'm filling in. She might be getting
a job closer to home.

384
00:42:32,836 --> 00:42:37,215
Why plastic?
- What are you trying to do to me?

385
00:42:37,382 --> 00:42:41,469
What do you mean?
- Look, elephant girl.

386
00:42:41,636 --> 00:42:47,267
Go get Carol or something.
Just have her do my one meal here.

387
00:42:47,434 --> 00:42:50,520
I'll pay whatever you want.

388
00:42:52,855 --> 00:42:55,190
Do it.

389
00:42:57,776 --> 00:43:01,238
Bryan. Code blue.

390
00:43:06,618 --> 00:43:10,956
Out. Just shut up and get out.

391
00:43:11,706 --> 00:43:17,879
I'll be quiet.
Just let me stay here. No problem.

392
00:43:18,046 --> 00:43:22,341
Go get Carol.

393
00:43:22,884 --> 00:43:28,097
I'm not a prick.
You are. I'm not judging.

394
00:43:28,306 --> 00:43:33,393
This day has been a disaster.

395
00:43:34,144 --> 00:43:37,939
I'm not sure if I can handle this.
- Get out.

396
00:43:38,982 --> 00:43:45,447
Get out immediately
or there's going to be trouble.

397
00:44:00,669 --> 00:44:02,755
See you.

398
00:44:03,839 --> 00:44:06,217
It's about time.

399
00:44:08,052 --> 00:44:13,556
Carol's last name?
- Connelly.

400
00:44:21,272 --> 00:44:25,267
Does he visit often?
- Not really. Not any more.

401
00:45:15,573 --> 00:45:18,410
I'm hungry.

402
00:45:18,576 --> 00:45:21,897
You've ruined my whole day.
I haven't eaten.

403
00:45:21,997 --> 00:45:26,193
What are you doing here?
- This is not a sexist thing...

404
00:45:26,293 --> 00:45:29,713
Are you totally gone?
This is my home.

405
00:45:31,839 --> 00:45:37,511
I'm trying to keep emotion aside,
even though it's important.

406
00:45:37,678 --> 00:45:42,641
I have strong feelings on this.
- What?

407
00:45:42,808 --> 00:45:48,772
That I wasn't there? Do you have
any control over how creepy you get?

408
00:45:54,569 --> 00:45:58,322
Yes, I do.

409
00:45:59,198 --> 00:46:04,954
And to prove it... I have not
gotten personal, and you have.

410
00:46:05,747 --> 00:46:10,084
Why aren't you at work?
Are you sick?

411
00:46:12,210 --> 00:46:15,589
You don't look sick.

412
00:46:16,173 --> 00:46:19,885
Just tired and bitter.

413
00:46:21,845 --> 00:46:25,098
My son is sick.

414
00:46:27,601 --> 00:46:30,437
What about your mother?

415
00:46:30,978 --> 00:46:36,525
How do you know about her?
- I hear you talking while I wait.

416
00:46:36,692 --> 00:46:40,780
Mom, I finished my juice.
- One sec.

417
00:46:49,830 --> 00:46:52,123
How are you doing?

418
00:46:57,837 --> 00:47:00,173
You should answer me.

419
00:47:00,340 --> 00:47:05,185
Sorry, Melvin. I can't handle you
teaching my son manners.

420
00:47:08,056 --> 00:47:10,557
Back to life.

421
00:47:18,023 --> 00:47:20,817
What's wrong?

422
00:47:20,984 --> 00:47:27,282
Five one-thousand,
four one-thousand...

423
00:47:30,035 --> 00:47:34,080
...104.9.
- We're going on a cab ride.

424
00:47:36,165 --> 00:47:39,460
Look out, you guys.

425
00:47:40,586 --> 00:47:44,924
Look out.
We're okay. We're okay.

426
00:47:46,676 --> 00:47:49,220
Melvin. Wait.

427
00:47:50,221 --> 00:47:53,223
Melvin. Wait.

428
00:47:58,812 --> 00:48:02,148
Shut up, kids.

429
00:48:02,732 --> 00:48:05,860
Give us a lift, would you?

430
00:48:09,990 --> 00:48:13,325
Cover your mouth when you cough.

431
00:48:15,077 --> 00:48:20,624
Brooklyn Presbyterian Hospital.
- Hospital?

432
00:48:21,125 --> 00:48:26,422
Any chance you'll be back today?
- No. Stay away from me.

433
00:48:30,967 --> 00:48:36,764
We can't put this off any longer.
I feel terrible that I have to...

434
00:48:37,181 --> 00:48:41,561
Could you just leave the dog for a second?

435
00:48:43,354 --> 00:48:46,190
Sorry.

436
00:48:48,943 --> 00:48:54,072
What are those cards?
- Frank thought I should have notes.

437
00:48:55,073 --> 00:49:00,078
So I would maintain focus
and not terrify you.

438
00:49:00,245 --> 00:49:05,584
See? He's right.
I need the cards.

439
00:49:05,751 --> 00:49:07,751
SlMON, YOU'RE BROKE

440
00:49:14,216 --> 00:49:19,205
The medical bills are 61,000 now.
And the show didn't go well.

441
00:49:19,305 --> 00:49:24,268
I spoke to your parents.
They didn't hang up or anything.

442
00:49:24,477 --> 00:49:28,355
But they'd feel strange calling you.

443
00:49:28,522 --> 00:49:33,151
I can't call them. Come here, baby.

444
00:49:34,402 --> 00:49:36,402
Come here.

445
00:49:36,529 --> 00:49:40,450
Verdell? What's wrong?

446
00:49:40,617 --> 00:49:45,121
You miss the tough guy?
Well, here I am.

447
00:49:45,330 --> 00:49:50,400
Happy to see me, you little mop?
How about a ride down the chute?

448
00:49:50,500 --> 00:49:53,212
I'm sorry. I didn't mean that.

449
00:49:53,378 --> 00:49:56,131
I didn't mean that, sweetheart.

450
00:49:56,298 --> 00:49:58,298
Sorry...

451
00:49:59,468 --> 00:50:04,806
I'll be able to keep my apartment
and the studio, won't I?

452
00:50:07,476 --> 00:50:11,479
Oh, my God.

453
00:50:41,341 --> 00:50:45,787
Yes, you make us a lot of money.
But it's more appropriate...

454
00:50:45,887 --> 00:50:52,768
I need this.
Just say, 'Melvin, I'll try.'

455
00:50:55,562 --> 00:50:59,483
Melvin, I'll try.
- Thank you.

456
00:50:59,650 --> 00:51:06,031
My son just got accepted to Brown.
My husband was dying.

457
00:51:06,198 --> 00:51:12,078
Good, nice, thrilled, exciting.
You don't have to wait with me.

458
00:51:19,836 --> 00:51:27,385
I can't resist. I just have
so many questions I want to ask you.

459
00:51:27,552 --> 00:51:31,763
You have no idea
what your work means to me.

460
00:51:31,930 --> 00:51:34,558
What does it mean to you?

461
00:51:34,850 --> 00:51:39,780
That somebody out there knows
what it's like to be in here.

462
00:51:40,689 --> 00:51:43,239
God, this is like a nightmare.

463
00:51:43,817 --> 00:51:47,904
Come on.
Just a couple of questions.

464
00:51:51,240 --> 00:51:55,578
How do you write women so well?
- I think of a man.

465
00:51:55,786 --> 00:52:00,332
And I take away reason and accountability.

466
00:52:31,778 --> 00:52:34,243
Mom.
- ln here, Mrs. Connelly.

467
00:52:34,323 --> 00:52:37,534
Please, what?
- I'm...

468
00:52:37,701 --> 00:52:40,370
Tell me.
- Dr. Bettes.

469
00:52:40,537 --> 00:52:45,459
Not your name. Where is he?
- He's in the bathroom.

470
00:52:46,001 --> 00:52:50,571
What's wrong? You know there are
doctors that come to your house?

471
00:52:50,671 --> 00:52:53,466
I'm home.

472
00:52:53,633 --> 00:52:58,223
I didn't know you had an admirer.
Oh, you met the gift.

473
00:52:59,096 --> 00:53:02,391
He's good. I'm an expert on doctors.

474
00:53:02,558 --> 00:53:05,561
Okay, doctor?

475
00:53:05,728 --> 00:53:09,439
My wife is Melvin Udall's publisher.

476
00:53:09,606 --> 00:53:15,053
I'm to take care of this little guy
because you are needed at work.

477
00:53:15,153 --> 00:53:19,491
What kind of work do you do?
- I'm a waitress.

478
00:53:19,699 --> 00:53:23,662
ln Manhattan.
- Dr. Bettes?

479
00:53:23,870 --> 00:53:26,331
Excuse me.

480
00:53:27,874 --> 00:53:32,194
I'm sorry it took so long.
- I couldn't find it, either.

481
00:53:32,294 --> 00:53:38,759
Could you get this to the lab?
I want it back today.

482
00:53:38,926 --> 00:53:45,140
Did you say 'today'?
- Yes. Let's sit down.

483
00:53:46,058 --> 00:53:51,562
These are the receipts from
all the prescriptions for the year.

484
00:53:51,729 --> 00:53:57,402
The calendar.
- This is a calendar of days.

485
00:53:57,568 --> 00:54:00,697
And how he felt.
- Good.

486
00:54:00,905 --> 00:54:05,602
How long has he had the problem?
- Since forever. Six months old.

487
00:54:05,702 --> 00:54:08,454
Have they done blood tests?

488
00:54:08,621 --> 00:54:12,416
When he was well?
- No.

489
00:54:12,582 --> 00:54:15,877
And how about skin testing?
- No.

490
00:54:16,044 --> 00:54:19,047
No standard scratch test?
- No.

491
00:54:19,256 --> 00:54:24,803
They said my plan didn't cover it.
Why? Should they have?

492
00:54:26,221 --> 00:54:29,390
Fucking HMO bastard pieces of shit.

493
00:54:31,392 --> 00:54:35,062
I'm sorry.
- That's their technical name.

494
00:54:37,231 --> 00:54:43,529
Once the tests come back,
is there someone we should talk to?

495
00:54:43,696 --> 00:54:47,450
Me.
My home number is on the card.

496
00:54:48,617 --> 00:54:51,578
His home number.

497
00:54:56,666 --> 00:54:59,919
What?
- Your home...

498
00:55:03,590 --> 00:55:09,261
Can we get you anything else?
- No, thank you.

499
00:55:09,428 --> 00:55:13,307
Couple of female slaves?

500
00:55:13,473 --> 00:55:18,228
There's still a lot of tests I need to do.

501
00:55:18,395 --> 00:55:22,191
Whatever I find out,
I promise you, -...

502
00:55:22,357 --> 00:55:27,457
...from now on your son is going
to feel a great deal better.

503
00:55:35,786 --> 00:55:37,997
Doc.

504
00:55:42,585 --> 00:55:46,631
That's good.

505
00:55:51,968 --> 00:55:56,164
Let me know about the costs.
One way or another we'll...

506
00:55:56,264 --> 00:56:00,226
The costs are going to be considerable.

507
00:56:00,393 --> 00:56:05,315
But Mr. Udall wants to be billed.

508
00:56:08,234 --> 00:56:10,903
That's wonderful.

509
00:56:14,239 --> 00:56:17,785
Thank you for everything, Nora.

510
00:56:18,077 --> 00:56:23,347
Forgive my crankiness. I'll call
when things get back on track.

511
00:56:30,880 --> 00:56:36,302
What's wrong?
- Who's going to walk Verdell?

512
00:56:38,346 --> 00:56:40,348
No.

513
00:56:55,070 --> 00:56:59,199
ls he dead yet?
- No.

514
00:57:00,075 --> 00:57:06,206
Would there be any way you would
be willing to walk his dog for him?

515
00:57:06,581 --> 00:57:12,795
Absolutely.
- You're a wonderful man.

516
00:57:14,004 --> 00:57:20,261
Two o'clock would be a good time.
Here is the key in case he's asleep.

517
00:57:21,512 --> 00:57:26,809
Open his curtains for him
so he can see God's beautiful work.

518
00:57:26,976 --> 00:57:32,005
And he'll know that even things
like this happen for the best.

519
00:57:32,105 --> 00:57:36,801
Did you learn to talk like this in
a 'Sailor, wanna hump-hump'-bar?

520
00:57:36,901 --> 00:57:40,301
Or is this your last shot at his whisky?

521
00:57:40,321 --> 00:57:44,741
Sell crazy someplace else.
We're all stocked up here.

522
00:57:52,791 --> 00:57:58,755
No. A goofy man is behind this.
You can't block out that man.

523
00:57:58,922 --> 00:58:04,447
Do you really want to go back to
emergency, where they can't help?

524
00:58:04,636 --> 00:58:09,599
This lets a crazy man into our lives.

525
00:58:12,310 --> 00:58:15,605
You know how this will turn out.

526
00:58:15,813 --> 00:58:21,338
This is not like a string of pearls.
You don't send this one back.

527
00:58:25,615 --> 00:58:27,950
Right?

528
00:58:32,996 --> 00:58:38,001
No. I do, I understand.
Listen. I have to go, okay?

529
00:58:38,918 --> 00:58:42,839
FRlENDS TO ASK FOR MONEY

530
00:58:43,506 --> 00:58:45,634
Bye.

531
00:58:46,259 --> 00:58:48,259
Bye-bye.

532
00:58:52,139 --> 00:58:54,391
What a day...

533
00:58:54,767 --> 00:58:57,853
Maybe I'll bring him some food by.

534
00:58:58,020 --> 00:59:00,773
Thank you for walking him.

535
00:59:02,691 --> 00:59:08,155
Excuse me, I'm not feeling well.
- This place smells like shit.

536
00:59:08,322 --> 00:59:10,490
Go away.

537
00:59:10,782 --> 00:59:16,120
This cleaning lady doesn't..?
- Please, just leave.

538
00:59:17,705 --> 00:59:22,668
What happened to your friends?
- Get out of here.

539
00:59:28,049 --> 00:59:32,828
There's nothing worse than having
to feel this way in front of you.

540
00:59:32,928 --> 00:59:37,682
Nellie.
Your a disgrace to depression.

541
00:59:38,850 --> 00:59:44,689
Rot in hell, Melvin.
- No need to stop being a lady.

542
00:59:44,898 --> 00:59:48,298
You'll be back on your knees in no time.

543
00:59:56,784 --> 01:00:00,037
ls this fun for you?

544
01:00:00,538 --> 01:00:06,585
It keeps getting better and better.
I'm losing my apartment, Melvin.

545
01:00:06,752 --> 01:00:12,277
Frank wants me to beg my parents,
who haven't called me, for help.

546
01:00:12,549 --> 01:00:14,549
And I won't.

547
01:00:14,592 --> 01:00:17,887
I don't want to paint any more.

548
01:00:18,263 --> 01:00:21,558
The life I was trying for, is over.

549
01:00:21,766 --> 01:00:27,564
The life I had is gone
and I'm feeling sorry for myself.

550
01:00:28,106 --> 01:00:33,631
It's high times for you, isn't it?
The gay neighbour is terrified.

551
01:00:34,194 --> 01:00:36,613
Terrified.

552
01:00:48,291 --> 01:00:52,295
I was trying to give you a boost.

553
01:00:52,461 --> 01:00:57,216
Lucky you.
You're here for rock bottom.

554
01:00:57,383 --> 01:01:01,762
You absolute horror of a human being.

555
01:01:14,441 --> 01:01:19,446
The one thing I'll do for you
might cheer you up.

556
01:01:19,654 --> 01:01:22,115
Get out.

557
01:01:22,449 --> 01:01:26,478
You want to know why the dog
prefers me? It's not affection.

558
01:01:26,578 --> 01:01:29,246
It's a trick.

559
01:01:31,248 --> 01:01:34,543
I keep bacon in my pocket.

560
01:01:35,085 --> 01:01:37,296
See?

561
01:01:43,010 --> 01:01:48,931
We'll both call him. You'll see.
It's a trick.

562
01:01:57,273 --> 01:02:00,651
Come here, Verdell.

563
01:02:05,448 --> 01:02:07,991
Come on.

564
01:02:08,366 --> 01:02:10,368
Come here.

565
01:02:15,624 --> 01:02:19,544
Just a stupid dog.

566
01:02:22,756 --> 01:02:26,843
Could you leave now? Please?

567
01:02:28,928 --> 01:02:32,473
I don't get it.

568
01:04:08,856 --> 01:04:10,856
Mr. Udall.

569
01:04:12,651 --> 01:04:16,113
Carol the waitress?
- Yes.

570
01:04:25,914 --> 01:04:30,844
The doctors gave me your address.
I'm sorry about the hour.

571
01:04:36,174 --> 01:04:39,177
If you...

572
01:04:41,763 --> 01:04:48,810
If it's about thanking me...
- That's not why I'm here.

573
01:04:49,019 --> 01:04:54,232
Though it's nice to talk to
a real doctor about Spencer.

574
01:04:56,860 --> 01:05:00,989
Note. Put it in a note.

575
01:05:09,580 --> 01:05:15,002
I have a hairdryer.
- Why did you do this for me?

576
01:05:19,173 --> 01:05:24,428
So you'd come back to work.
- That sounds strange.

577
01:05:27,722 --> 01:05:31,309
I'm worried you did this...

578
01:05:46,449 --> 01:05:51,370
Are you waiting for me to say something?

579
01:05:53,747 --> 01:05:56,333
Look...

580
01:05:58,001 --> 01:06:03,549
I'll be there tomorrow.
- I need to clear this up now.

581
01:06:04,967 --> 01:06:07,760
Clear what up?

582
01:06:09,136 --> 01:06:14,392
I'm not going to sleep with you.
I will never sleep with you.

583
01:06:15,935 --> 01:06:17,937
Not ever.

584
01:06:22,441 --> 01:06:26,779
I'm sorry, but...

585
01:06:28,655 --> 01:06:34,160
...we don't open
for the no-sex oaths until 9 a.m.

586
01:06:35,078 --> 01:06:41,167
I'm not kidding.
- Anything else?

587
01:06:42,794 --> 01:06:47,715
Just... thank you.

588
01:06:53,137 --> 01:06:56,265
So you will be at work tomorrow?

589
01:06:58,809 --> 01:07:01,270
Yes.

590
01:07:16,034 --> 01:07:19,454
'Never', she said.

591
01:07:37,721 --> 01:07:41,641
I took a chance you were up.

592
01:07:41,975 --> 01:07:45,312
I brought you some Chinese soup.

593
01:07:47,521 --> 01:07:49,690
Thanks.

594
01:08:06,123 --> 01:08:09,876
I've never been this tired in my life.

595
01:08:16,633 --> 01:08:20,178
I haven't been sleeping.

596
01:08:21,471 --> 01:08:26,810
I haven't been clear in my head
or felt like myself.

597
01:08:29,645 --> 01:08:32,272
I'm in trouble.

598
01:08:32,731 --> 01:08:35,526
It's not just the tiredness.

599
01:08:36,026 --> 01:08:41,281
Sick. Nauseous.
- Sleepy.

600
01:08:41,448 --> 01:08:47,703
Everything looks distorted
and everything inside aches.

601
01:08:47,912 --> 01:08:51,707
You can barely find the will to complain.

602
01:08:55,753 --> 01:08:59,340
I'm glad we did this.

603
01:09:00,091 --> 01:09:03,261
Good talking to you.

604
01:09:10,976 --> 01:09:17,315
Still writing that thank-you note?
- How do you spell 'conscience'?

605
01:09:17,482 --> 01:09:20,819
C-O-N-S-C-I-E-N-C-E.

606
01:09:20,986 --> 01:09:26,241
Look, I got Sean to babysit
so we could go out.

607
01:09:26,408 --> 01:09:30,318
I don't feel safe
leaving Spencer with someone.

608
01:09:30,411 --> 01:09:35,936
Spencer's okay. Start finding
something to do with your free time.

609
01:09:36,750 --> 01:09:40,212
Sean, are you hungry?

610
01:09:41,130 --> 01:09:47,427
We got pizza. Sausage, pepperoni.
You want to make this later?

611
01:09:49,178 --> 01:09:52,765
We are going out, like people do.

612
01:09:54,726 --> 01:10:01,107
If you can't feel good about
this break and step out a little, -...

613
01:10:01,274 --> 01:10:06,429
...then you ought to have Mr. Udall
send you over a psychiatrist.

614
01:10:06,529 --> 01:10:10,354
I don't need one.
I know what's going on here.

615
01:10:12,659 --> 01:10:18,707
I must finish this letter first.
This can't be right? Con-science?

616
01:10:19,332 --> 01:10:21,626
Carol.

617
01:10:25,881 --> 01:10:28,883
What?

618
01:10:43,856 --> 01:10:46,983
It's very weird not feeling that...

619
01:10:47,650 --> 01:10:51,988
...stupid panic thing inside me.

620
01:10:52,697 --> 01:10:56,493
Without that,
I start thinking about myself.

621
01:10:56,701 --> 01:11:00,121
And what good
does that ever get anybody?

622
01:11:02,832 --> 01:11:06,443
Today on the bus
there was this adorable couple.

623
01:11:06,543 --> 01:11:09,338
And I felt myself...

624
01:11:10,672 --> 01:11:14,301
...giving them a dirty look.

625
01:11:14,760 --> 01:11:20,849
I just had no idea.
Everything was...

626
01:11:27,772 --> 01:11:30,441
Go ahead.

627
01:11:31,609 --> 01:11:35,029
Moving in the wrong direction.

628
01:11:35,738 --> 01:11:42,161
Away from a time when I remembered
what it was like to have a man...

629
01:11:42,328 --> 01:11:44,705
...to hold fucking...

630
01:11:48,917 --> 01:11:52,754
...hands with.

631
01:11:54,506 --> 01:12:00,720
I felt almost really bad
that Dr. Bettes is married.

632
01:12:04,266 --> 01:12:09,706
Which is probably why I make Spence
hug me more than he wants to.

633
01:12:11,230 --> 01:12:16,235
He has to make up for
his Mom not getting any.

634
01:12:20,531 --> 01:12:26,327
Who needs these thoughts?
- So, are you frustrated?

635
01:12:26,494 --> 01:12:31,582
Leave me be.
What is it you want?

636
01:12:31,749 --> 01:12:38,089
Does getting me thinking about all
that's wrong have some purpose?

637
01:12:39,465 --> 01:12:43,219
Really, Mom, what is it you want?

638
01:12:43,594 --> 01:12:48,098
What?
- I want us to go out.

639
01:13:17,376 --> 01:13:22,339
Thank you.
- I'll send you a thank-you note.

640
01:13:29,012 --> 01:13:31,723
That's why you brought me here?

641
01:13:31,890 --> 01:13:37,520
Well, it's not even mine.
Simon has enough on his mind.

642
01:13:37,687 --> 01:13:41,691
But the dog did throw up twice last night.

643
01:13:41,858 --> 01:13:47,237
Take him to the vet.
- I did. His stomach's out of whack.

644
01:13:47,404 --> 01:13:51,399
They need him a couple of days.
- Well, do it...

645
01:13:51,867 --> 01:13:53,911
Sorry.

646
01:13:54,203 --> 01:13:59,082
This is for later.
- What's this?

647
01:14:00,167 --> 01:14:04,004
It's a note.
- A note?

648
01:14:04,213 --> 01:14:07,715
A thank-you note.
- No thank you.

649
01:14:07,882 --> 01:14:12,637
You can read it later.
- No thank-you note. No, no.

650
01:14:15,556 --> 01:14:18,684
Thank you.

651
01:14:24,232 --> 01:14:30,946
She's nice.
- Yeah, really nice.

652
01:14:33,323 --> 01:14:38,423
Shouldn't that be a good thing,
saying, 'No thanks required'?

653
01:14:39,996 --> 01:14:43,875
Sure looks like it went over, too.

654
01:14:45,001 --> 01:14:48,545
Look at you.

655
01:14:48,754 --> 01:14:54,051
You're making the rounds.
Simon says you brought him soup.

656
01:14:58,347 --> 01:15:01,892
What?
- You think I'm a mark...

657
01:15:02,101 --> 01:15:07,171
You helped with the dog. I'm as
concerned about Simon as you are.

658
01:15:07,271 --> 01:15:10,416
Concerned?
- He needs more than money.

659
01:15:10,441 --> 01:15:15,305
He must go to Baltimore to ask
his parents for money tomorrow.

660
01:15:15,405 --> 01:15:19,242
They have to help. It's the rules.

661
01:15:19,409 --> 01:15:23,121
That's great. Let them help him.

662
01:15:24,914 --> 01:15:26,998
Only...

663
01:15:27,165 --> 01:15:32,546
...I got a painter coming through,
so I'm out.

664
01:15:33,130 --> 01:15:38,260
Can you drive him?
- Think white and get serious.

665
01:15:40,220 --> 01:15:43,390
Take my car? A convertible.

666
01:15:44,808 --> 01:15:48,769
Do you drive?
- Yes. But I'm not doing it.

667
01:15:48,936 --> 01:15:51,772
Getting loud.

668
01:15:53,315 --> 01:15:58,571
He wants me to take his car...
- I want your problems.

669
01:15:58,737 --> 01:16:04,177
Somebody offers me a convertible
so I can get out of this city...

670
01:16:09,706 --> 01:16:13,960
Go ahead, girl.
- Okay. I'll do it.

671
01:16:14,127 --> 01:16:19,674
I'll take him. Get him packed.
Tomorrow morning I'll take him.

672
01:16:24,512 --> 01:16:29,933
I'll see you tomorrow.
Let's not drag this out.

673
01:16:35,105 --> 01:16:40,715
If there's some health foundation
for people like you, let me know.

674
01:16:41,069 --> 01:16:45,656
Last-word freak.
- Good luck, lady.

675
01:16:46,866 --> 01:16:50,202
Anything else?
- Yeah.

676
01:16:52,371 --> 01:16:57,131
I'm going to give my queer neighbour
a lift to Baltimore.

677
01:17:00,671 --> 01:17:05,884
What I did for you...
It's working out?

678
01:17:08,303 --> 01:17:12,015
What you did changed my life.

679
01:17:12,891 --> 01:17:15,101
No.

680
01:17:15,560 --> 01:17:18,188
No thank-you note.

681
01:17:18,396 --> 01:17:23,751
Well, part of what I said in this
entire history of my life -...

682
01:17:24,069 --> 01:17:29,365
...is that you have done more
for my mother, my son...

683
01:17:29,573 --> 01:17:33,202
...and me than anybody else ever has.

684
01:17:33,369 --> 01:17:37,194
I'm just going to read you this part of it...

685
01:17:37,873 --> 01:17:43,754
'That makes you the most generous
person I ever met in my life.'

686
01:17:43,921 --> 01:17:48,549
'And you're going to be
in our daily prayers, forever.'

687
01:17:49,967 --> 01:17:52,053
Lovely.

688
01:17:53,221 --> 01:17:57,600
I also wrote one part...
I wrote that I was sorry.

689
01:17:59,686 --> 01:18:04,173
I was talking about how I was sorry
when I got mad at you -...

690
01:18:04,273 --> 01:18:08,510
...when you told my son
that he ought to answer back.

691
01:18:08,610 --> 01:18:15,158
I wrote that I was sorry about that.
I'm sorry for that night...

692
01:18:15,700 --> 01:18:19,830
...when I said that I was never...

693
01:18:19,996 --> 01:18:25,584
I'm sorry for every time your food
was cold and you had to wait.

694
01:18:25,918 --> 01:18:32,716
And I'm sorry for never spotting the
human being that did this for us.

695
01:18:34,885 --> 01:18:38,097
I'll just start from the beginning.

696
01:18:38,305 --> 01:18:41,917
'I have not been able to express
my gratefulness to you.'

697
01:18:42,017 --> 01:18:47,605
'The word grateful doesn't begin
to tell you what I feel.'

698
01:18:51,317 --> 01:18:55,321
That's nice of you. Thank you.

699
01:18:58,241 --> 01:19:01,119
Thank you.

700
01:19:09,668 --> 01:19:13,380
Now I want you to do something for me.

701
01:19:20,345 --> 01:19:25,308
I'm sorry. Didn't I say 'what'?
I thought I did.

702
01:19:28,895 --> 01:19:33,232
What?
- I want you to go on this trip.

703
01:19:33,399 --> 01:19:36,986
No, sir.
- I can't do this without you.

704
01:19:37,194 --> 01:19:44,493
He might pull the stiff one-eye
on me. I need you to chaperone.

705
01:19:44,702 --> 01:19:51,166
You said you liked convertibles.
Now I'm on the hook. Two days.

706
01:19:51,333 --> 01:19:57,088
I can't. My son.
- Bettes said he's doing fine.

707
01:19:58,006 --> 01:20:05,262
Melvin, I'd rather not.
- Write a note. Ain't she sweet?

708
01:20:05,429 --> 01:20:11,518
I need a hand and where is she?
- Your help obligates me?

709
01:20:12,227 --> 01:20:16,440
ls there any other way to see it?

710
01:20:18,067 --> 01:20:20,361
No.

711
01:20:25,073 --> 01:20:30,536
Here's a little suitcase.
Shocked that it's being used.

712
01:20:39,462 --> 01:20:42,607
There's no way to pack for this trip.

713
01:21:06,112 --> 01:21:09,657
You're still coming, aren't you?
- Yes.

714
01:21:10,950 --> 01:21:15,079
Melvin, exactly where are we going?

715
01:21:15,246 --> 01:21:19,734
Just south of Baltimore.
I know what you're going to say.

716
01:21:19,834 --> 01:21:23,087
I mean... I think I know.

717
01:21:23,921 --> 01:21:30,426
I'm not sure, but I think so.
- Should I bring something dressy?

718
01:21:32,887 --> 01:21:37,477
Will we be eating in restaurants
that have dress codes?

719
01:21:41,813 --> 01:21:43,815
Maybe...

720
01:21:44,149 --> 01:21:49,111
Yes. Let's... Let's.
- Okay.

721
01:21:52,197 --> 01:21:56,226
What did you think I'd ask?
- Whether crabs were in season now.

722
01:21:56,326 --> 01:22:00,622
Okay, then. Goodnight.

723
01:22:05,835 --> 01:22:10,131
Anything unusual in his diet?
- No.

724
01:22:10,590 --> 01:22:16,637
Everybody gets their own cage?
Put him in with that one.

725
01:22:18,222 --> 01:22:20,222
Lip kiss.

726
01:22:23,019 --> 01:22:28,523
I love you. I'll miss you...
Real sensitive.

727
01:22:29,482 --> 01:22:33,737
Bye.
- Call when you're settled.

728
01:22:41,411 --> 01:22:45,748
Have a good time.
- Don't run.

729
01:22:46,206 --> 01:22:50,961
Have fun, but don't run.

730
01:22:55,049 --> 01:22:58,619
I'm sorry I'm not taking you.
- So am I, Frank.

731
01:22:58,719 --> 01:23:01,513
Give me a hug.

732
01:23:02,556 --> 01:23:05,183
Everything's going to be okay.

733
01:23:05,391 --> 01:23:11,064
Soak it up. It's your last chance
for a hug for a few days.

734
01:23:16,778 --> 01:23:19,280
Hello.

