977
01:52:22,473 --> 01:52:27,687
You've got real problems.
- I know. I'm a little bit nervous.

978
01:52:27,854 --> 01:52:31,524
Suddenly everything seems so easy.

979
01:52:31,899 --> 01:52:35,486
Carol, a load has been lifted.

980
01:52:37,905 --> 01:52:41,645
One night wih me.
- You think you're kidding.

981
01:52:45,328 --> 01:52:50,625
No choice.
- I've got a gift for you.

982
01:52:50,792 --> 01:52:54,588
Let me see... Gorgeous.

983
01:52:55,505 --> 01:53:00,326
Do it. And get the dog picked up. I
can't believe he let it stay there.

984
01:53:00,426 --> 01:53:03,220
Goodbye.

985
01:53:03,429 --> 01:53:05,598
Your luck's running.

986
01:53:05,765 --> 01:53:10,895
They sub-let your place.
You're homeless.

987
01:53:11,061 --> 01:53:16,734
Frank's got a line on a new place.
- Where?

988
01:53:17,401 --> 01:53:20,945
Does it matter?

989
01:53:22,030 --> 01:53:25,033
No, it doesn't.

990
01:53:25,950 --> 01:53:29,037
I'm fine. Like the hat?

991
01:53:30,163 --> 01:53:32,163
I'm sorry.

992
01:53:47,054 --> 01:53:49,473
FOR EMERGENCY USE ONLY...

993
01:54:04,654 --> 01:54:09,909
I don't want to hear that music.
- You said you liked it.

994
01:54:12,370 --> 01:54:18,709
This one has a meaning.
- I don't want to hear it.

995
01:54:40,980 --> 01:54:45,192
Here's the keys to my apartment.

996
01:54:45,359 --> 01:54:49,613
Go up there and wait
and I'll take Carol home.

997
01:54:49,780 --> 01:54:54,326
I'll take a bus.
- No, I'll take you.

998
01:54:59,747 --> 01:55:02,667
Can you come here?

999
01:55:02,834 --> 01:55:06,696
I don't care what you did for me.
- What's wrong?

1000
01:55:06,796 --> 01:55:12,321
I don't want to know you any more.
All you do is make me feel bad.

1001
01:55:15,555 --> 01:55:18,516
You have my number.

1002
01:55:19,891 --> 01:55:24,062
Let him take you home.
- Don't want to.

1003
01:55:25,147 --> 01:55:28,275
I love you.
- I love you too.

1004
01:55:36,783 --> 01:55:39,535
Don't say anything.

1005
01:55:43,122 --> 01:55:48,562
I've got to get a hold of Frank
and see where I'm hanging my hat.

1006
01:55:49,545 --> 01:55:53,370
I think you're going to have to camp it here.

1007
01:55:53,424 --> 01:55:56,719
There's Verdell.

1008
01:56:04,934 --> 01:56:08,521
Mommy and Daddy are home.

1009
01:56:10,023 --> 01:56:14,277
Sorry. You're fun to mess with.

1010
01:56:15,445 --> 01:56:20,849
They rented your place furnished.
Jackie said she'd bring your things.

1011
01:56:20,949 --> 01:56:25,829
They were going to set you up
in here. It's an extra room.

1012
01:56:25,996 --> 01:56:31,001
It's got good light.
- I'm coming.

1013
01:56:35,964 --> 01:56:39,926
It's nice. Looks good.

1014
01:56:40,134 --> 01:56:47,725
They've even got your music,
paintings, paints.

1015
01:56:47,892 --> 01:56:50,782
I have to say they did a good job.

1016
01:56:53,147 --> 01:56:59,277
It's going to be okay.
Cosy, huh?

1017
01:57:04,074 --> 01:57:08,662
Thank you, Melvin.
You overwhelm me.

1018
01:57:15,961 --> 01:57:19,755
I love you.

1019
01:57:23,842 --> 01:57:30,516
I'd be the luckiest guy alive
if that did it for me.

1020
01:57:42,652 --> 01:57:46,280
Make yourself at home.

1021
01:57:47,615 --> 01:57:50,243
Anything else in the bag?

1022
01:57:50,410 --> 01:57:54,163
But I was playing soccer
while you were away.

1023
01:57:54,330 --> 01:57:57,834
I love my cookbook.

1024
01:57:58,000 --> 01:58:03,004
It's got wonderful recipes.
It says something with a shark.

1025
01:58:03,171 --> 01:58:08,427
Shark with a bite.
Would you like that, Spencer?

1026
01:58:08,593 --> 01:58:12,078
And some cookies here
called Wasps' Nests.

1027
01:58:14,725 --> 01:58:18,186
Where is my big hairy boy?

1028
01:58:18,395 --> 01:58:23,190
Where is he?
Where is my beautiful boy?

1029
01:58:23,357 --> 01:58:25,526
Sweetheart.

1030
01:58:25,693 --> 01:58:29,155
Oh, you're in bed.
- No, no.

1031
01:58:32,533 --> 01:58:39,747
I just didn't think Verdell should
get too comfortable sleeping here.

1032
01:58:39,914 --> 01:58:43,585
The dog's already comfortable.

1033
01:58:47,589 --> 01:58:49,589
ls this okay?

1034
01:58:51,509 --> 01:58:55,054
Hello... Hi, it's me.

1035
01:58:55,513 --> 01:59:00,767
He took me in.
It's Carol for you.

1036
01:59:00,934 --> 01:59:05,772
Jackie brought it all over...
- Just take the dog.

1037
01:59:06,773 --> 01:59:08,773
Take the dog.

1038
01:59:12,112 --> 01:59:17,618
Come on. Move fast. Don't limp.
- Good luck.

1039
01:59:33,966 --> 01:59:37,094
Howare you doing?
- Not so hot.

1040
01:59:37,261 --> 01:59:43,016
Why? What's wrong?
- Was I sensible or hard on you?

1041
01:59:43,308 --> 01:59:49,606
Maybe both.
- Are you being cute or crazy now?

1042
01:59:49,773 --> 01:59:54,444
Cute.
- You don't have to answer.

1043
01:59:54,653 --> 01:59:57,072
Just listen to me.

1044
01:59:57,822 --> 02:00:02,184
It's really something
that you're looking after Simon.

1045
02:00:02,284 --> 02:00:07,956
And what I said on the street...
That was a bad thing to say.

1046
02:00:08,165 --> 02:00:14,296
It made me sick to my stomach.
It was a bad thing to say.

1047
02:00:14,672 --> 02:00:19,384
And I'd be lying if I didn't say
I enjoy your company.

1048
02:00:21,010 --> 02:00:27,141
But you do bother me.
And I know it's better for me...

1049
02:00:27,350 --> 02:00:32,005
...to not have contact with you
because you're not ready.

1050
02:00:32,105 --> 02:00:36,718
You're an old guy to not be ready.
And I'm too old to ignore that.

1051
02:00:36,818 --> 02:00:42,489
But there were extraordinary
kindnesses that did take place.

1052
02:00:49,162 --> 02:00:52,124
Anyway. Thanks for the trip.

1053
02:00:53,917 --> 02:00:56,253
Goodnight.

1054
02:00:56,420 --> 02:00:59,505
Okay if I say something now?

1055
02:01:03,551 --> 02:01:06,137
Go ahead.

1056
02:01:07,138 --> 02:01:11,308
I should have danced with you.

1057
02:01:14,395 --> 02:01:17,857
Goodnight.

1058
02:01:37,417 --> 02:01:42,004
Are you going to talk to me?
- I'm coming.

1059
02:01:52,431 --> 02:01:57,477
What did she say?
- That I'm a great guy.

1060
02:01:57,644 --> 02:02:01,898
And she doesn't want contact with me.

1061
02:02:03,024 --> 02:02:05,902
I'm dying here.

1062
02:02:07,194 --> 02:02:13,117
Because... you love her.
- No.

1063
02:02:13,284 --> 02:02:16,604
And you people
are supposed to be sensitive?

1064
02:02:16,704 --> 02:02:21,191
Then you tell me why.
You're the one who's 'dying here'.

1065
02:02:21,291 --> 02:02:24,961
Let me sleep on it.
- Oh, come on.

1066
02:02:25,128 --> 02:02:28,923
I'll figure it out.
- Please...

1067
02:02:30,342 --> 02:02:36,723
I'm stuck.
I can't get back to my old life.

1068
02:02:38,849 --> 02:02:43,837
She's evicted me from my life.
- Did you really like it that much?

1069
02:02:43,937 --> 02:02:47,149
It's better than this.

1070
02:02:47,316 --> 02:02:51,845
If you're going to give me hope,
you've got to do better.

1071
02:02:51,945 --> 02:02:55,891
If you can't be mildly interesting,
then shut up.

1072
02:02:55,991 --> 02:03:00,061
I'm drowning here.
And you're describing the water.

1073
02:03:00,161 --> 02:03:03,247
Picking on me won't help.

1074
02:03:04,374 --> 02:03:08,252
If that's true,
I'm really in trouble.

1075
02:03:08,419 --> 02:03:12,465
Do you know where you're lucky?

1076
02:03:17,220 --> 02:03:20,889
You know who you want.

1077
02:03:21,056 --> 02:03:27,145
I would take your seat any day.
Do something. Go over there.

1078
02:03:27,312 --> 02:03:32,609
Tonight. It's not always good
to let things calm down.

1079
02:03:32,776 --> 02:03:36,780
You can do this, Melvin.

1080
02:03:36,947 --> 02:03:40,157
Tell her how you feel.

1081
02:03:40,366 --> 02:03:44,578
I'm charged.
- Yes, you are.

1082
02:03:44,745 --> 02:03:49,442
She might kill me if I go there.
- Then stay. I'll read you a story.

1083
02:03:49,542 --> 02:03:55,492
The best thing going for you is your
willingness to humiliate yourself.

1084
02:03:55,506 --> 02:03:59,259
Go over there.
Do this. Catch her off guard.

1085
02:04:09,060 --> 02:04:11,729
Thanks a lot.

1086
02:04:13,398 --> 02:04:16,192
Here I go.

1087
02:04:25,242 --> 02:04:28,036
What's wrong?

1088
02:04:29,621 --> 02:04:32,749
I forgot to lock the door.

1089
02:05:51,032 --> 02:05:54,687
What do you want?
- I'm sorry I woke you up.

1090
02:05:54,827 --> 02:05:58,121
I wasn't asleep.

1091
02:06:01,458 --> 02:06:04,461
What a break.

1092
02:06:05,420 --> 02:06:09,091
ls it a secret what you're doing here?

1093
02:06:11,343 --> 02:06:14,304
I had to see you.

1094
02:06:17,473 --> 02:06:19,767
Because?

1095
02:06:22,186 --> 02:06:26,232
It relaxes me.

1096
02:06:26,690 --> 02:06:30,928
I'd feel better sitting outside
your apartment on the curb -...

1097
02:06:31,028 --> 02:06:35,407
...than any other place
I can think of or imagine.

1098
02:06:35,574 --> 02:06:38,201
That's overstating.

1099
02:06:38,368 --> 02:06:44,249
I'd rather be sitting inside so I
don't get my feet in the gutter.

1100
02:06:44,415 --> 02:06:49,963
Stop. Why can't I just have
a normal boyfriend? Why?

1101
02:06:50,129 --> 02:06:53,954
A regular boyfriend
who doesn't go nuts on me.

1102
02:06:54,050 --> 02:06:57,427
Everybody wants that.
It doesn't exist.

1103
02:07:01,056 --> 02:07:06,186
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to interrupt.

1104
02:07:12,317 --> 02:07:15,529
Boyfriend...

1105
02:07:18,406 --> 02:07:23,703
Come on in and try
not to ruin everything by being you.

1106
02:07:23,911 --> 02:07:28,040
Maybe we could live
without the wisecracks?

1107
02:07:31,419 --> 02:07:35,172
Maybe we could.

1108
02:08:00,070 --> 02:08:05,075
It feels a little confined here.
Let's take a walk.

1109
02:08:07,995 --> 02:08:13,542
It's four in the morning.
A walk sounds a little screwy to me.

1110
02:08:14,418 --> 02:08:19,589
If you don't mind.
- Well, if you need an excuse...

1111
02:08:20,423 --> 02:08:24,758
There's a bakery on the corner
that'll be open soon.

1112
02:08:24,802 --> 02:08:30,558
That way we're not screwy,
but two people that like warm rolls.

1113
02:08:54,873 --> 02:09:01,295
What are you doing?
- I want you to hear that song.

1114
02:09:08,677 --> 02:09:13,516
And darling I'm neverlonely...

1115
02:09:13,682 --> 02:09:17,185
...wheneveryou're in sight...

1116
02:09:18,019 --> 02:09:20,019
Thank you.

1117
02:09:21,523 --> 02:09:24,818
I was...

1118
02:09:38,705 --> 02:09:43,961
I'm sorry.
Whatever this is won't work.

1119
02:09:52,386 --> 02:09:54,805
I'm...
- What?

1120
02:09:56,973 --> 02:09:59,767
I'm feeling better.

1121
02:09:59,934 --> 02:10:06,816
It may seem that way now,
but you don't know me all that well.

1122
02:10:07,692 --> 02:10:10,736
I'm not the answer for you.

1123
02:10:10,903 --> 02:10:14,991
I've got a compliment for you.
- You know what?

1124
02:10:15,157 --> 02:10:19,035
Let me talk.

1125
02:10:25,625 --> 02:10:29,379
I might be the only person on the earth -...

1126
02:10:29,587 --> 02:10:32,657
...that knows
you're the greatest woman on earth.

1127
02:10:32,757 --> 02:10:40,347
I might be the only one who knows
how amazing you are.

1128
02:10:40,723 --> 02:10:44,893
And how you are with Spencer.
Spence.

1129
02:10:46,103 --> 02:10:50,316
And in every single thought you have.

1130
02:10:50,482 --> 02:10:57,196
How you almost always mean something
that's about being straight or good.

1131
02:10:58,448 --> 02:11:02,285
Most people miss that about you.

1132
02:11:02,618 --> 02:11:07,857
I wonder how they can watch you
bring their food and clear tables -...

1133
02:11:07,957 --> 02:11:12,362
...and never get that they just met
the greatest woman alive.

1134
02:11:12,462 --> 02:11:17,591
And the fact that I get it
makes me feel good...

1135
02:11:18,508 --> 02:11:22,721
...about me.

1136
02:11:29,144 --> 02:11:35,609
ls that something
that it's bad for you to be around?

1137
02:11:44,784 --> 02:11:47,203
No.

1138
02:11:49,955 --> 02:11:53,209
I'm going to grab you?

1139
02:11:53,375 --> 02:11:58,645
I didn't mean for that to be
a question. I'm going to grab you.

1140
02:12:21,527 --> 02:12:24,404
I know I can do better than that.

1141
02:12:47,843 --> 02:12:51,722
Better. Definitely better.

1142
02:12:55,726 --> 02:12:58,728
See?

1143
02:13:12,742 --> 02:13:17,454
Want something?
- Warm rolls.

1144
02:13:26,005 --> 02:13:28,215
Excuse us.

